726966f-a.title: Queens: Jamaica Avenue - Carpenter Avenue
726966f-a.text:
Jamaica Ave., at the S.E. corner of Carpenter Ave., showing in
a set of two views the George Alexander House of 1891. Other owners
were A. Colyer, 1860; Mrs. Meven, 1873; J.M. Alexander, 1891; and
the above mentioned Alexander. In 1883 the house was not in its
Dresent shape. At this time it was an orphanage probably conducted
by Mrs. Leven.
May 1923.
View 2: April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
